"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-olympic-table-tennis-rules-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The summer Olympics have arrived, and you know what that means\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094table tennis at the absolute highest level!\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 108, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether you are an enjoyer ofForrest Gump,Balls of Fury, or merely grew up with an easily accessible ping-pong table there are myriad reasons to get excited to watch table tennis at the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 307, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course, the rules are a little different for the Olympics than in Grandpa's garage playing a family tournament at Thanksgiving.\", \"from\": 309, \"to\": 439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 378, \"end\": 385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grampa_Simpson\", \"score\": 0.9974440379446439, \"rank\": 0.002562511738313475, \"text\": \"Grandpa\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grampa_Simpson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grampa_Simpson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The basics are familiar, insofar as the objective of the game is to defeat the opponent by earning points in a manner quite like tennis.\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 576, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the particulars are where Olympic table tennis diverges from the games that take place in Bryant Park.\", \"from\": 577, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here we endeavor to inform you of those differences and paint a full picture of what table tennis will look like at the 2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Visually, Olympic table tennis is not all that dissimilar from standard ping-pong.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 909, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Games are played on a rectangular table, split into two halves by a short net that checks in at 15.25 centimeters, per Olympic regulations.\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 1049, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The paddle is more commonly referred to as a \\\"racquet\\\" in international play and boasts two rubber sides\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 one black and one red.\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1180, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ball itself will either be orange or white with a weight of 2.7 grams and a diameter of 40 millimeters.\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To determine who goes first, table tennis turns to a classic\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094an old-fashioned toin coss.\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The umpire will flip a coin and the winner will get to choose whether they'd like to serve first, receive first, or choose a side of the table, at which point the decision to serve or receive will fall on the loser of the coin toss.\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1615, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Once the order of operations is determined by the coin toss, the game will get underway by one player serving to the other.\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But there are rules in place to prevent any sort of trickery from occurring on the serve.\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1830, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to theOlympics website, \\\"The server has to hold the ball with an open palm, toss it up and strike it in a manner that the ball bounces first on the server\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s side of the table before bouncing over the net to the other side.\\\"\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 2067, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In singles, the server is permitted to hit the ball to any part of the table.\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In doubles, though, all serves must go diagonally across the table.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2213, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, on returns, a player must wait until the ball is bounced to hit it with a paddle.\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If they hit it while still in the air, a foul is called.\", \"from\": 2303, \"to\": 2359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ultimate objective is for one player to reach the target score quicker than the other.\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In order to do that, points must be scored.\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A point is scored in two different ways.\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first way for a player to score a point is to hit the ball to an area where the opponent cannot return it.\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2648, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Doing so will earn the hitting player a point, so long as the ball legally bounces off the table on the side of the opponent first.\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A point is also scored if an opponent hits the ball into the net or misses the table entirely.\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2876, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In that scenario the receiving player, not the hitting player, gets a point for their opponent's miscue.\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 2981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In order to win a match of Olympic table tennis, one player must reach 11 points before the other.\", \"from\": 2983, \"to\": 3081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In an instance where the score is tied, 10-10, the first player to reach 11 willnotwin.\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3169, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the winner will be the first player to go up bytwopoints.\", \"from\": 3170, \"to\": 3236, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But one win does not secure a full Olympic victory.\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In singles, table tennis games are usually best-of-seven matches.\", \"from\": 3290, \"to\": 3355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So the first player to get to 11 points (or win by two) four times will be declared winner of the game.\", \"from\": 3356, \"to\": 3459, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The best way to fully understand the concepts above is to see them in action.\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3538, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thus, we present a 10-minute highlight compilation of Olympic table tennis.\", \"from\": 3539, \"to\": 3614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are now fully prepared to enjoy Olympic table tennis.\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 3675, \"to\": 3701, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Liam McKeone is a senior writer for the Breaking and Trending News team at Sports Illustrated.\", \"from\": 3702, \"to\": 3860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3766, \"end\": 3770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liam_Gallagher\", \"score\": 0.9999999953024599, \"rank\": 4.6723667791864e-09, \"text\": \"Liam\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liam_Gallagher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liam_Gallagher\"}, {\"begin\": 3841, \"end\": 3859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2031694443439676e-18, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has been in the industry as a content creator since 2017, and prior to joining SI in May 2024, McKeone worked for NBC Sports Boston and The Big Lead.\", \"from\": 3861, \"to\": 4013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3978, \"end\": 3995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Boston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Sports Boston\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Boston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Boston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to his work as a writer, he has hosted the Press Pass Podcast covering sports media and The Big Stream covering pop culture.\", \"from\": 4014, \"to\": 4150, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A graduate of Fordham University, he is always up for a good debate and enjoys loudly arguing about sports, rap music, books and video games.\", \"from\": 4151, \"to\": 4292, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4165, \"end\": 4183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fordham_University\", \"score\": 0.9978289201916721, \"rank\": 0.0021607635085289655, \"text\": \"Fordham University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fordham_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fordham_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McKeone has been a member of the National Sports Media Association since 2020.\", \"from\": 4293, \"to\": 4371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4326, \"end\": 4359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Sports_Media_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Sports Media Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Sports_Media_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Sports_Media_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC.\", \"from\": 4373, \"to\": 4450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 4451, \"to\": 4473, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only.\", \"from\": 4474, \"to\": 4550, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands.\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4678, \"end\": 4696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2031694443439676e-18, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit.\", \"from\": 4746, \"to\": 4834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\", \"from\": 4835, \"to\": 4967, \"entities\": []}]}"